	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />From what I've heard one reason is the actual circuit design of the SNES may have made it easier to clone than the NES. I recall someone saying something about various bits, being analog on the NES where as SNES is pretty much digital all the way. I forget who said it. But apparently SNES clones seem to be pretty accurate, some do play the games with coprocessors just fine.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
